## Project Architecture

### Overview
The EcoCold website is a React-based application designed for managing cold storage facilities. It provides two main user interfaces:
- **Farmer Interface**: For farmers to book storage space and manage their produce
- **Operator Interface**: For operators to monitor facilities, manage bookings, and handle alerts

### Architecture Pattern
- **Component-Based Architecture**: Modular React components for reusability
- **CSS Modules**: Scoped styling to prevent conflicts
- **Functional Components**: Modern React patterns with hooks
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach with breakpoints

### Directory Structure
```
ecocold application/
├── src/
│   ├── components/          # Reusable components
│   │   ├── charts/         # Chart components for monitoring
│   │   ├── hub/           # Hub-related components
│   │   ├── layout/        # Layout components (Navbar, Footer, Sidebar)
│   │   └── ui/           # UI components (Button, Card, Input, Modal)
│   ├── data/             # Static data files
│   ├── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
│   ├── pages/            # Page components
│   │   ├── auth/         # Authentication pages
│   │   ├── farmer/       # Farmer interface pages
│   │   └── operator/     # Operator interface pages
│   ├── routes/           # Route configuration
│   ├── styles/           # Global styles
│   └── App.jsx           # Main application component
├── public/               # Static assets
├── package.json          # Dependencies and scripts
├── vite.config.js        # Vite configuration
└── README.md            # Project documentation
```

